			    		<h1>Why 80% of Traders and Investors fail in the first 3 years</h1>
			    		<h5>
			    			<ol>
			    				<li><strong><em>Looking for a Holy Grail:</em></strong> Do not skip around from on method, system, indicator or service to the next. Trying to find instant gratification usually ends up in disappointment.</li>
			    				<li><strong><em>Not sticking to a plan:</em></strong> Without sticking to a plan, you start reacting to the market instead of anticipating the market. The market can be chaotic and confusing, specially for someone without a specific plan of action.</li>
			    				<li><strong><em>Improper mind set:</em></strong> Humans are emotional creatures by nature, being emotional in an uncertain environment is never a good idea. Almost any book that you get a hold of on trading psychology will hit home the idea of more discipline and less emotion.</li>
			    				<li><strong><em>Improper trade size:</em></strong> Poor account sizing and risking too much per trade is a sure way to fail. You cannot think of trading as a sprint; it is more like a marathon, and a quite long one at that. You will lose trades here and there but it is how you handle those losses that counts.</li>
			    				<li><strong><em>Poor risk to reward ratio:</em></strong> The two reasons traders end up with a poor risk to reward is that they don't have a trading plan, and the can't hold their winners, but they hold their losers.</li>
			    				<li><strong><em>Over trading:</em></strong> If you're trading just for the sake of trading, then you are probably over trading. You must be patient and trade when things line up for you and not trade every time the market moves.</li>
			    				<li><strong><em>Not taking trading seriously:</em></strong> It is amazing that most people will not treat trading as they would with other money making endeavors. They think if they read a couple of "for dummies" books and download some software that they can be successful.</li>
			    				<li><strong><em>Not having a successful mentor:</em></strong> Any successful trader once had a mentor, coach or service help them to formulate a plan and strategy to learn how to be successful in the trading world.</li>
			    			</ol>
