			    			</ul>
			    		</h5>
			    		<h5>Basically, with active trader status, you gain benefits on the tax side of everything. Without active trader status, if you have a net loss of over $3,000 you can only write off up to $3,000 of that net loss. Here at Prime we have a different solution to all of this, we do what is called setting up a dual entity.</h5>
